OL,6,F"Kamran was and always remained
OL,7,Fentirely unaware of why (the 16-year-
OL,8,Fold) backed up by his friend decided
OL,9,Fto focus his violent rage upon him.
OL,11,F"Kamran was simply in the wrong place
OL,12,Fat the wrong time and the reality you
OL,13,Fmay think is that anybody who stood in
OL,14,Fthe way of (the 16-year-old) that
OL,15,Fnight faced mortal peril.
OL,17,F"The extent of the aggression shown by
OL,18,F(the 16-year-old) was obvious to all
OL,19,Fwho witnessed it, including (the 17-
OL,20,Fyear-old) who nevertheless decided to
OL,21,Fback him up."
